  </comment>

<p><app>Disk Usage Analyzer</app> is a graphical analyzer application that 
shows the usage and capacity of the whole filesystem or any specific folder, 
like <gui>Home folder</gui> or any other local or remote one. 
It also auto-detects in real-time changes as far as any mounted/unmounted device.</p> 

<p>By default, <app>Disk Usage Analyzer</app> starts with a quick representation 
of the total filesystem capacity used and the available one; ready to 
<link xref="scan-home"><gui>Scan Home Folder</gui></link>, <link xref="scan-folder"><gui>
Scan a folder</gui></link> or <link xref="scan-remote"><gui>Scan a remote</gui></link>.</p>

<p><gui>Total file system capacity</gui> and <gui>Total file system usage</gui> 
are presenting in rectangles charts by default; but, you can change it by clicking 
<link xref="view-ring">View as a ring</link>.</p>

